formalText: Patient seeks power over the conversation .
She is 35 but she talks about how she feels 23.
She thinks she is really wonderful and great.
She says she doesn't need sleep anymore.
Her thought have been causing her to think more intensely.
She feels at this time fantastic, cuz God's telling her that she's doing a really good job.
This is the first time in her life where she has felt this high level of energy and bright ideas.
She has felt very sad and low in the past.
She finds most people less clever than her.
A doctor has put her on Prozac, she says it didn't do anything for her.
She's a Potter and own a business with her sister.
In fact, her sister didn't say go away and she told her to get the fuck away from her.
She is the only person  in her family to feel this way
